SSyynnooppssiiss
       getfilename format filename

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  getfilename  program  asks the user for the name of a
       file in the format specified by  format  and  copies  that
       file to the filename given as the second argument.

       getfilename  provides  functionality  to  programs such as
       mailto, which reference mailcap files.  For  example,  the
       following line in a mailcap file allows mailto to help the
       user  include  PostScript  in  outgoing   mail:   applica-
       tion/postscript;  lpr  -Pipa  %s;  description="Include  a
       Postscript File"; compose="getfilename Postscript %s"

